FuncDef:
The undo send-time command deletes the send-time configuration.
The undo receive-time command deletes the receive-time configuration. The undo send-time command deletes the send-time configuration. The undo receive-time command deletes the receive-time configuration. By default, no send-time is configured.


By default, no receive-time is configured. By default, no send-time is configured. By default, no receive-time is configured.
ParentView: weekly Key-ID view,yearly Key-ID view,monthly Key-ID view
ExtraInfo: A keychain consists of multiple key IDs and different key IDs are active in different time periods. In this manner, authentication algorithms can be dynamically switched, improving protocol data transmission security. To make different key IDs take effect in different time periods, you need to configure the sending time and receiving time of each key ID.
